org.microbean.launcher

Class ClasspathExporter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.microbean.launcher.ClasspathExporter

  • @Singleton
public final class ClasspathExporter
extends Object
    A special-purpose class that converts a list of Maven-style artifact coordinates into a Set of classpath URIs when it is added to a CDI container.
    Author:
    Laird Nelson
    See Also:
    getClasspath(), getRemainingCommandLineArguments()

      ClasspathExporter()
      Creates a new ClasspathExporter.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Set<URI> getClasspath()
      Returns an unmodifiable Set of URIs representing Java classpath elements that resulted from examining the user-supplied artifact path—a list of Maven-style artifact coordinates.
      List<Dependency> getDependencies()
      Returns the List of Dependency instances that will be used by this class to compute the eventual classpath returned by the getClasspath() method.
      String[] getRemainingCommandLineArguments()
      Returns a String array representing any command line arguments that this class did not "consume" as it tried to determine the user-supplied artifact path.
      List<Dependency> produceDependencies(CommandLine commandLine)
      A producer method that produces an application-scoped List of Dependency instances that represent Maven-style artifact coordinates from either explicitly-set Dependency instances or command-line arguments or system properties.
      void setDependencies(List<Dependency> dependencies)

    • Method Detail

      • produceDependencies

        @Produces
 @ApplicationScoped
public final List<Dependency> produceDependencies(CommandLine commandLine)
        A producer method that produces an application-scoped List of Dependency instances that represent Maven-style artifact coordinates from either explicitly-set Dependency instances or command-line arguments or system properties.

        This method never returns null.

        Parameters:
        commandLine - a CommandLine instance; may be null in which case an empty List will be returned
        Returns:
        a non-null List of Dependency instances
        See Also:
        setDependencies(List), getDependencies()

      • getDependencies

        public final List<Dependency> getDependencies()
        Returns the List of Dependency instances that will be used by this class to compute the eventual classpath returned by the getClasspath() method.

        This method may return null.

        Returns:
        a List of Dependency instances, or null
        See Also:
        setDependencies(List)

      • setDependencies

        public final void setDependencies(List<Dependency> dependencies)
        Sets the List of Dependency instances that will be used by this ClasspathExporter to compute the classpath returned by the getClasspath() method.

        Users of this class should not feel obligated to call this method. If this method is not explicitly called, this class will infer the list of dependencies from command line arguments and system properties.

        Parameters:
        dependencies - a List of Dependency instances; may be null
        See Also:
        getDependencies(), getClasspath()

      • getClasspath

        public final Set<URI> getClasspath()
        Returns an unmodifiable Set of URIs representing Java classpath elements that resulted from examining the user-supplied artifact path—a list of Maven-style artifact coordinates.

        This method never returns null.

        Returns:
        a non-null, unmodifiable Set of URIs representing Java classpath elements

      • getRemainingCommandLineArguments

        public final String[] getRemainingCommandLineArguments()
        Returns a String array representing any command line arguments that this class did not "consume" as it tried to determine the user-supplied artifact path.

        This method will never return null.

        Returns:
        a non-null String array representing any command line arguments that this class did not "consume" as it tried to determine the user-supplied artifact path
